The vision, priorities and main principles of energy sector development policy
* The vision of the development policy is to become electric energy exporting country with
* The following priorities of energy sector development policy is identified based on current
	* Reliability and safety of energy supply;
	* Efficiency, productivity;
	* Environmental sustainability and green development.
	* The following main principles are applied in setting of the strategic objectives and goals
	* reliable energy supply and energy security;
	* ensure sustainable economic development;
	* build favorable condition on increase population life standard;
	* be environmentally friendly;
	* be efficient and economic;
	* be rational for science and knowledge based.

In the scope of energy reliability and security:
* Ensure energy safety and supply reliability;
* Develop mutually beneficial cooperation with regional countries;
* Develop human resource and form human capacity in the energy sector.

In the scope of increase of efficiency and productivity:
* Transform energy sector into private based competitive market scheme;
* Introduce and implement policy for support of implementation of innovative and

The following financing sources will applied in implementation of the State energy sector policy:
* state private sector cooperation, national and international investment;
* financing from stock market;
* state budget financing, investment programs;
* cooperation with international financing organizations;
* loans;
* other sources.
